HEADWORD: Hemigamous
<hw>He*mig"a*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hemi-</ets> + Gr. <?/ marriage.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having one of the two florets in the same spikelet neuter, and the
other unisexual, whether male or female; -- said of grasses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

